\subsection{Drift}
\label{sec:2a}

Drift in solids. terminal velocity, somewhat.

initially, straight line (in log-linear graph). slope called mobility
($\mu$). $v = \mu E$. Doesn't do that forever. Other things start
happening as well, and you end up getting a limit.

$\mu$ depends on collisions. higher T $\implies$ lower $\mu$. higher doping
