\section{PN Junction}
\label{sec:3}
Diode has two regions, N, P. Two carrier types: n, p. two types of
conduction: drift, diffusion.

Ionization from diffusion generates voltage difference, induces electric
field. Drift pushes electrons back and cancels out diffusion. This is
equilibrium, i.e. no net flow of electrons or holes.

